Summary:
- Primary programming language: Java
- Primary development framework: Spring Boot (Spring Boot 2.x)

Key evidence:
- Build configuration:
  - pom.xml shows Spring Boot as the parent (spring-boot-starter-parent) with version 2.3.5.RELEASE.
  - Dependencies include spring-boot-starter-web, spring-boot-starter-data-jpa, spring-boot-starter-security, and spring-boot-starter-test.
  - Java version specified as 11 (<java.version>11</java.version>).
  - The project is a Maven project (pom.xml) with a Spring Boot Maven plugin (spring-boot-maven-plugin) in the build section.
- Main application:
  - The source tree contains src/main/java/com/urcodebin/api/UrCodebinApiApplication.java and a line indicating @SpringBootApplication, confirming a Spring Boot application.
- Dockerization:
  - Dockerfile uses a multi-stage build starting from a Maven/OpenJDK image to build the jar, then runs the app from a JRE image, with a CMD invoking java -jar app.jar and a prod profile (-Dspring.profiles.active=prod).
- Project structure and purpose:
  - The repository layout (src/main/java, src/main/resources, etc.) and the README describe a REST API backend, consistent with a Spring Boot web service using JPA (as evidenced by spring-boot-starter-data-jpa) and MySQL driver dependency.

What this implies:
- The project is a Java-based REST API backend built with Spring Boot 2.x, using Maven as the build tool, targeting Java 11, and packaging as an executable Spring Boot jar. It likely exposes REST endpoints (spring-boot-starter-web) and uses JPA for data access (spring-boot-starter-data-jpa), with security features (spring-boot-starter-security). The Dockerfile indicates containerized deployment with a prod profile.
